    "# 3. Trading signal & rolling backtest\n",
    "\n",
    "Following Tadi & Witzany (2025), §\"Implementation methodology\" and §\"Key assumptions and limitations\".\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.1 Rolling formation/trading scheme\n",
    "\n",
    "The static fit in §1-§2 above used the **whole** dataset, which leaks future information into pair selection and parameter estimation. The paper's actual procedure is:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "   ┌──── formation (3 weeks = 504h) ────┐ ┌─ trading (1 week = 168h) ─┐\n",
    "   │  re-run OLS β, ADF/KSS, Kendall τ  │ │  use frozen β             │\n",
    "   │  re-fit marginals + copula         │ │  use frozen marginals     │\n",
    "   │  output (sym1, sym2, β1, β2,       │ │  use frozen copula        │\n",
    "   │          marginal1/2, copula)      │ │  generate signals, trade  │\n",
    "   └─────────────────────────────────────┘ └────────────────────────────┘\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Each cycle steps forward by 1 week. The formation period **trains** the model; the trading period only **applies** the frozen parameters.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.2 Mispricing index from conditional copula\n",
    "\n",
    "For each $(u_t, v_t)$ in the trading week:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "h^{1|2}_t = P(U_1\\le u_{1t}\\,|\\,U_2=u_{2t}) = \\frac{\\partial C(u_1,u_2)}{\\partial u_2}\\bigg|_{(u_t,v_t)}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "h^{2|1}_t = P(U_2\\le u_{2t}\\,|\\,U_1=u_{1t}) = \\frac{\\partial C(u_1,u_2)}{\\partial u_1}\\bigg|_{(u_t,v_t)}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Mispricing index $MI^{j|k}_t = h^{j|k}_t - 0.5$. Far from $0.5$ means strong divergence from the modeled copula.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.3 Trading rules (paper Table 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "| Condition | Action |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| $h^{1\\|2} < \\alpha_1$ AND $h^{2\\|1} > 1-\\alpha_1$ | **Open** long $S^1$, short $S^2$ |\n",
    "| $h^{1\\|2} > 1-\\alpha_1$ AND $h^{2\\|1} < \\alpha_1$ | **Open** short $S^1$, long $S^2$ |\n",
    "| $\\|h^{1\\|2}-0.5\\| < \\alpha_2$ AND $\\|h^{2\\|1}-0.5\\| < \\alpha_2$ | **Close** all positions |\n",
    "| End of trading week | **Force-close** any open positions |\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.4 Translation to coin trades (paper Table 4)\n",
    "\n",
    "Since $S^i = \\mathrm{BTC} - \\beta^i P^i$:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Long $S^1$: long 1 BTC, short $\\beta^1$ units of coin $1$\n",
    "- Short $S^2$: short 1 BTC, long $\\beta^2$ units of coin $2$\n",
    "\n",
    "The 1 BTC long and 1 BTC short cancel — net exposure is only on coins $1$ and $2$. BTC is the *reference* asset, never traded directly.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.5 Position sizing (paper §\"Key assumptions\")\n",
    "\n",
    "At the start of each trading week, fix quantities so that each leg's notional ≤ 20,000 USDT:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Q_i = \\frac{20{,}000}{P_i^{\\text{open}}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "These quantities are held constant through the week. Taker fee 0.04% per leg, charged at both open and close.\n",
    "\n",
    "If formation period yields fewer than two stationary pairs, that week is **skipped** (no position taken).\n"
   ]
